        "text": "Norman Mailer’s groundbreaking 1968 “The Armies of the Night” is being made into a film to be directed by Joe Berlinger, who was behind the “Paradise Lost” documentaries about the infamous West Memphis Three case.\n\nMailer’s son Michael Mailer will produce the adaptation of the Pulitzer and National Book Award-winning “nonfiction novel” with Jon Kamen and Stanley Buchthal, from a script by Michael’s brother John Buffalo Mailer.\n\nThe book follows the 1967 march on the Pentagon. Michael says the film will “be told from the point of view of a documentary team following [Norman Mailer] around during the march,” as well as events “leading up to and following” it.\n\nCasting’s underway for the roles of Mailer and William F. Buckley Jr. “The challenge is finding a leading man who can pull off Norman,” Michael figures. “It’s a tricky mix of fiery intelligence, acerbic wit, existential bad-ass-ness and pugilistic fervor. You can probably count those guys on one hand.”"
